🧠 Key Features
High CMRR Differential Input Stage
INA333 instrumentation amplifier for microvolt-level signal acquisition
Symmetric input routing to preserve signal integrity
Precision Analog Processing
Active full-wave rectification for accurate EMG envelope extraction
Peak detection using RC hold network for stable signal representation
Event-Driven Architecture
Comparator-based threshold detection
Generates digital EMG_WAKE signal for external MCU (e.g., ESP32)
Enables low-power operation (wake-on-EMG concept)
Low-Noise PCB Design
Optimized component placement (stage-wise layout)
Differential signal routing
Ground plane with stitching vias
Decoupling and bulk capacitors for power stability
Modular Interface
Header-based output for easy integration with microcontrollers
Exposed signals: INA_OUT, ABS_OUT, PEAK_OUT, EMG_WAKE
